WEBVTT

00:17.350 --> 00:25.859
**

00:30.530 --> 00:32.198
[tires squealing]
- [Quiet] Jesus!

00:32.240 --> 00:34.367
If you're tired,
just pull over.

00:34.409 --> 00:35.952
- Look, I'm on a schedule.

00:35.994 --> 00:38.288
Besides, it'd be
a lot easier

00:38.329 --> 00:40.290
if I didn't have to sit here
in complete silence.

00:45.670 --> 00:47.213
Knock-knock.

00:47.255 --> 00:49.549
- What are you doing?
- I'm telling a joke.

00:49.591 --> 00:51.384
I say, "Knock-knock."
You say, "Who's there?"

00:51.426 --> 00:53.386
- So, I should already know
the joke before you tell it?

00:53.428 --> 00:55.388
That's idiotic.
- It's a classic joke structure

00:55.430 --> 00:57.432
with a little audience
participation.

00:57.474 --> 00:59.601
I say, "Knock-knock."
You say, "Who's there?"

00:59.642 --> 01:02.354
I say somethin' like, "Orange."
You say, "Orange who?"

01:02.395 --> 01:04.481
Then I hit you
with the punch line.

01:04.522 --> 01:06.983
- Why the fuck am I
talking to an orange?

01:07.025 --> 01:08.276
- Why are you
making this so hard?

01:08.318 --> 01:09.986
Just say,
"Who's there?"

01:10.028 --> 01:12.072
Ready?

01:12.113 --> 01:13.281
Knock-knock.
[rumbling]

01:13.323 --> 01:16.576
- Do you hear that?
- Yes, it's me knocking.

01:16.618 --> 01:19.412
[rumbling]
Wait. I hear it, too.

01:21.373 --> 01:24.501
Hold on.
Activating stealth mode.

01:28.046 --> 01:32.801
[rumbling]

01:32.842 --> 01:34.260
[horns honking]

01:34.302 --> 01:36.179
Oh, shit! They have
stealth mode, too!

01:36.221 --> 01:37.889
- [Quiet]
What the hell?

01:37.931 --> 01:39.516
Just turn around.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.934
- [John Doe] I can't.
They're everywhere.

01:40.975 --> 01:42.102
- [Quiet] Oh, my god.

01:42.143 --> 01:43.144
- [John Doe] Move!
- [Quiet] Oh, my god!

01:43.186 --> 01:44.270
Fuck! Fuck!
- [John Doe] Move! Move!

01:44.312 --> 01:45.730
- Shoot them.
- [John Doe] With what?

01:45.772 --> 01:48.441
The law stripped Evelyn
back down to factory settings.

01:50.151 --> 01:51.778
Oh, I guess
they missed that one.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.029
[cocking gun]
Hey, don't waste my shells.

01:53.071 --> 01:54.406
I only have four
of those.

01:54.447 --> 01:56.366
[gunshot and ricochet]

01:56.408 --> 01:59.285
Shooting a steel door, smart.
Now, I only have three.

01:59.327 --> 02:01.871
[horns honking]

02:01.913 --> 02:03.415
[tires squealing]
[screaming]

02:03.456 --> 02:05.208
- Go faster! Go faster!
- Okay! Okay!

02:05.250 --> 02:06.876
- [Quiet] Oh, no, no, no!
Go slower! Go slower!

02:06.918 --> 02:07.961
- Make up your mind!

02:08.003 --> 02:09.921
[screaming]

02:09.963 --> 02:11.172
Whoa!

02:11.214 --> 02:14.801
[tires squeal]

02:14.843 --> 02:16.344
[gate slams]

02:22.559 --> 02:24.644
Hey!
You'll get it back

02:24.686 --> 02:26.312
when you act mature enough
to handle it.

02:26.354 --> 02:27.605
- Okay, dad.
[blows raspberry]

02:27.647 --> 02:30.775
- [Watts] Come on out,
milkman!

02:30.817 --> 02:32.318
We ain't
gonna hurt you.

02:32.360 --> 02:34.821
- Yeah, right. Huh.
Fell for that before.

02:34.863 --> 02:36.448
- You have?

02:36.489 --> 02:38.366
- [Miranda] You know,
if we wanted to,

02:38.408 --> 02:40.118
you'd be dead already.

02:40.160 --> 02:41.536
Look, I swear,

02:41.578 --> 02:44.330
I swear on
granny's steering wheel

02:44.372 --> 02:45.957
no harm is gonna
come to you.

02:45.999 --> 02:48.376
We just--
we wanna flap lips.

02:48.418 --> 02:50.962
- I don't even know
what that means.

02:51.004 --> 02:54.466
But fine.
We're comin' out.

03:02.182 --> 03:04.309
- I'm sorry that
we-we snatched ya up

03:04.351 --> 03:05.518
the way that we did,

03:05.560 --> 03:07.187
but I saw that placard
on your rump,

03:07.228 --> 03:08.646
and I was like,
we gotta talk.

03:08.688 --> 03:10.523
I'm Watts.
I run these rigs.

03:10.565 --> 03:14.194
- John. This is Quiet.
She don't talk.

03:14.235 --> 03:16.613
- Motherfucker, eat shit.
- Much.

03:16.654 --> 03:19.366
Hello. Hey.

03:19.407 --> 03:21.493
- My blood missiles?

03:21.534 --> 03:23.411
Honey, those are outside
your weight class.

03:23.453 --> 03:28.041
Oh, she's a beaut.

03:28.083 --> 03:29.959
Hmm.

03:30.001 --> 03:32.379
Did you install this limited
slip differential yourself?

03:32.420 --> 03:35.173
- Sure did. Got it off of a--
- It's backwards.

03:35.215 --> 03:36.925
[chuckles]

03:36.966 --> 03:39.719
- Wow, did you invite me here
to insult me or to talk?

03:39.761 --> 03:43.181
- Yeah, it's not really me
who wants a word.

03:43.223 --> 03:45.183
Lock it up.

03:45.225 --> 03:49.688
- Whoa.
- Whoa! [yelping]

03:49.729 --> 03:50.897
- Come on.

03:50.939 --> 04:05.870
**

04:05.870 --> 04:09.082
**

04:09.124 --> 04:11.084
Welcome to convoy.

04:11.126 --> 04:14.170
- Wow!
Okay, I'm impressed.

04:14.212 --> 04:15.088
- [Watts] Our founders
drove these semis

04:15.130 --> 04:16.506
when the walls
went up.

04:16.548 --> 04:18.883
Figure we'd better keep movin'
than be sittin' ducks.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.719
No offense, Bella.

04:20.760 --> 04:22.762
- That's a chicken.
- No, it's not.

04:22.804 --> 04:25.974
And now, our little family is
around about 30 rigs all told.

04:26.016 --> 04:27.267
- And you never stop.

04:27.308 --> 04:28.685
How the hell
do you fuel up?

04:28.727 --> 04:31.730
- Oh, nothing goes to waste,
even our waste.

04:31.771 --> 04:34.315
You see,
we take our doodies

04:34.357 --> 04:36.234
and turn 'em into fuel.
- Yeah, we get it.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.485
- Somethin' tells me

04:37.527 --> 04:39.612
I don't wanna taste
your lemonade either.

04:39.654 --> 04:41.448
- Okay, I'm gonna have
to ask y'all to stay here.

04:41.489 --> 04:42.532
Feel free
to look around.

04:42.574 --> 04:43.992
I need a lift
to the sleeper car.

04:53.043 --> 04:54.461
- So, how'd you
lose yours?

04:54.502 --> 04:57.297
Metal shear?
Angle grinder?

04:57.339 --> 04:59.966
Oh, somethin' worse.

05:00.008 --> 05:03.303
- It's fine.
- Oh, hmm.

05:03.345 --> 05:08.224
Well, uh, let me see
what I got here.

05:08.266 --> 05:13.021
Oh, this oughta fit.
- I can't pay.

05:13.063 --> 05:14.689
- Not lookin' for pay.

05:14.731 --> 05:17.859
Just think you could shine
a bit more, if you want.

05:24.449 --> 05:27.911
Mm-hmm.
That's it.

05:27.952 --> 05:29.454
- Thanks.

05:29.496 --> 05:30.914
- Don't get it wet.

05:35.877 --> 05:37.796
- Hey, she's here.

05:44.094 --> 05:45.553
- Someone there?

05:45.595 --> 05:48.056
- I brought you
to the milkman, granny.

05:48.098 --> 05:50.308
[groans]

05:50.350 --> 05:52.811
- I'd get up
and shake your hands,

05:52.852 --> 05:55.939
but my get away sticks
ain't what they used to be.

05:58.233 --> 06:01.236
- Granny,

06:01.277 --> 06:03.613
your air tubes
go to nowhere.

06:07.492 --> 06:10.245
- Well, shit.

06:10.286 --> 06:12.914
I thought I had ya.

06:12.956 --> 06:15.417
[groans]

06:15.458 --> 06:19.295
This Goddamn metal bar
keeps stickin' in my ass.

06:19.337 --> 06:22.716
Uh, uh, hey,
be careful with that.

06:22.757 --> 06:27.262
Took me ages to write,
and I only got the one copy.

06:27.303 --> 06:28.471
- You did that
while driving?

06:28.513 --> 06:29.806
[laughing]

06:29.848 --> 06:33.893
- Sometimes you gotta
throw it in reverse.

06:33.935 --> 06:35.979
[laughing]

06:36.021 --> 06:39.357
Listen, milkman,
I know I don't look it,

06:39.399 --> 06:43.695
but my insides look like
a seven car pileup.

06:43.737 --> 06:46.948
I need you to go pick up
some medicine for me.

06:46.990 --> 06:48.950
- You want me
to make a run for free?

06:48.992 --> 06:50.869
You're up to your asshole
in drivers.

06:50.910 --> 06:51.911
Ask one of them.

06:51.953 --> 06:53.621
- Can't afford to lose
any of them.

06:53.663 --> 06:55.540
- The last milkman
never came back.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.792
The roads are rough these days
with the vultures,

06:57.834 --> 07:00.879
the lawmen,
the holy men.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.630
- Don't love the sound
of that last one.

07:02.672 --> 07:05.592
- Look, I don't have time
for scenic detours.

07:05.633 --> 07:07.385
I have
a very important delivery,

07:07.427 --> 07:09.095
and I got a long way
still to go.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.847
- I heard your ride

07:10.889 --> 07:14.517
is as naked as a baby
on its birthday.

07:14.559 --> 07:17.437
You ain't gonna get far,
you can't defend yourself.

07:17.479 --> 07:19.230
Well, let me
make it plain.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.107
You do this run
for me,

07:21.149 --> 07:22.400
I'll will
saddle you up

07:22.442 --> 07:25.403
with all the upgrades
we can supply.

07:25.445 --> 07:28.239
We will weld on some guns,
right now.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.617
Get the rest
when you get back.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.202
[spits]
Deal?

07:35.622 --> 07:37.791
- Only if I get those
red missiley things.

07:37.832 --> 07:40.460
- Mnh-mnh. My blood missiles--
they ain't for sale.

07:40.502 --> 07:42.837
- You can have one.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.631
- What, granny? Come on.
- Three.

07:44.673 --> 07:45.423
- Two.
- Twenty.

07:45.465 --> 07:46.675
- Zero.
- Zero.

07:48.760 --> 07:51.471
- Okay. [spits]
One it is.

07:51.513 --> 07:53.181
- Done.
[chuckles]

07:53.223 --> 07:55.183
Pickup is at our
pharmacist's.

07:55.225 --> 07:56.685
I'll write ya up
some directions.

07:56.726 --> 07:57.977
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

07:58.019 --> 07:59.604
You didn't tell me that
he's going to see her.

07:59.646 --> 08:01.606
- Where'd you think
he was goin'?

08:01.648 --> 08:05.318
Watts and the pharmacist
had a bit of a falling out.

08:05.360 --> 08:06.403
- Falling out?

08:06.444 --> 08:07.779
No, I pushed her
out of a truck.

08:07.821 --> 08:10.407
- Honey,
go weld somethin'.

08:10.448 --> 08:11.741
- I am.
I'm gonna weld somethin'.

08:11.783 --> 08:14.202
I'm gonna weld some guns
to your fucking Subaru.

08:14.244 --> 08:15.453
You fuckin'
son of a bitch.

08:15.495 --> 08:16.746
- What about Topeka?

08:16.788 --> 08:18.123
- Did you miss the fact

08:18.164 --> 08:20.208
that a semi swallowed us up
like a fuckin' whale?

08:20.250 --> 08:22.627
Now, the only way
I'm making it back to Chicago,

08:22.669 --> 08:25.213
is if Evelyn
is armed to the teeth,

08:25.255 --> 08:28.174
and now she's just gums.

08:28.216 --> 08:29.592
So, chill.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.261
I'll be back tomorrow.

08:31.302 --> 08:32.429
- Oh, no, no, no.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.014
I'm coming with you.
- Like hell you are.

08:34.055 --> 08:35.890
This is milkman business,
and you're not a milkman.

08:35.932 --> 08:37.976
[scoffs]
- If you die out there,

08:38.018 --> 08:39.978
I'm stuck here
with horndog granny.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.689
- Look, I'm not gonna die.
I give you my word.

08:42.731 --> 08:45.567
- I'm coming with you.
- Fine.

08:54.409 --> 08:55.243
- [John Doe]
"Three clicks past

08:56.453 --> 08:57.829
the oak of eight branches."
What are these?

08:57.871 --> 09:00.040
Directions to a pharmacist
or to a hidden treasure?

09:00.081 --> 09:01.374
Why couldn't she just say,
"Turn left?"

09:05.920 --> 09:08.882
So, what do you
think happened

09:08.923 --> 09:10.884
between Watts
and the pharmacist?

09:10.925 --> 09:12.844
- Don't know.
Don't care.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.721
- Oh, cool.

09:14.763 --> 09:18.016
See you got a new finger to go
with your robotic personality.

09:24.731 --> 09:33.990
**

09:34.032 --> 09:36.409
I bet that was
those holy men guys.

09:36.451 --> 09:37.452
- Oh, you think?

09:39.329 --> 09:40.497
Bad way to go.

09:40.538 --> 09:42.707
[scoffs]
- I've seen worse.

09:42.749 --> 09:44.751
Deskinned by butchers.

09:44.793 --> 09:47.671
Crushed to death
by monster trucks.

09:47.712 --> 09:49.005
That's plural.

09:49.047 --> 09:52.008
I knew a milkman that
fell asleep on an anthill,

09:52.050 --> 09:55.720
and those little shits ate 'em
alive from the insides out.

09:55.762 --> 09:58.807
Poor bastard betrayed
by his butthole.

09:58.848 --> 10:00.725
- Sounds like milkmen
don't live long.

10:00.767 --> 10:02.102
- We don't.

10:02.143 --> 10:03.770
You know, when I joined up
to be a milkman,

10:03.812 --> 10:05.105
I was skin and bones.

10:05.146 --> 10:07.524
You could play my ribcage
like a xylophone.

10:07.565 --> 10:10.318
I joined up to survive.

10:10.360 --> 10:13.279
I make my run.
I kill some vultures.

10:13.321 --> 10:16.616
I do whatever I have to
to see another sunrise.

10:16.658 --> 10:17.951
You know what
they told me

10:17.992 --> 10:19.953
when they gave me
this milkman I.D.?

10:19.994 --> 10:21.955
- Why would I know that?
I wasn't there.

10:21.996 --> 10:24.124
- You're messing
up the story.

10:26.876 --> 10:30.505
They told me
milkmen don't die old.

10:30.547 --> 10:34.884
But if I deliver this package
to New San Francisco,

10:34.926 --> 10:37.971
I might be the first.

10:38.013 --> 10:41.016
[bells tolling]

10:41.057 --> 10:43.059
- You hear those bells?

10:43.101 --> 10:45.145
- [John Doe] Holy men.

10:45.186 --> 10:48.606
Good thing they sound far away.
Let's haul ass.

11:07.500 --> 11:10.003
[knocking]
Hello?

11:13.256 --> 11:14.674
Anybody in there?
[knocking]

11:14.716 --> 11:16.176
- [Amber] Salutations.
[screaming]

11:17.719 --> 11:19.929
- [John Doe] Um, hi.

11:19.971 --> 11:22.974
We're here on, uh,
behalf of the convoy.

11:23.016 --> 11:24.517
- You're the pharmacist?

11:24.559 --> 11:26.561
- No, I'm Amber.

11:29.147 --> 11:33.026
Tea? It's gelsemium elegans.
I cut it this morning.

11:33.068 --> 11:38.782
Oh, you look
so thirsty.

11:38.823 --> 11:41.284
- I am.

11:41.326 --> 11:43.203
- The sun isn't
holding back today,

11:43.244 --> 11:45.038
are you,
you big yellow bastard?

11:45.080 --> 11:47.540
[giggles]
Bastard.

11:47.582 --> 11:50.085
Oh.

11:50.126 --> 11:53.463
So, you have refreshments.

11:55.048 --> 11:58.385
And I have questions.

11:58.426 --> 12:00.553
[retching]
- Quiet, what the fuck?

12:00.595 --> 12:02.097
[retching]

12:02.138 --> 12:05.225
- Oh, save your strength.

12:05.266 --> 12:07.394
You won't be able to move
for a little while.

12:14.317 --> 12:14.567
**

12:15.860 --> 12:17.904
- [John Doe] I knew this pickup
was a bad idea.

12:17.946 --> 12:20.740
Quiet, get my gun.
[wretches]

12:20.782 --> 12:22.867
- [Amber] Oh.

12:22.909 --> 12:27.288
So, why did you kill
the convoy's milkman?

12:27.330 --> 12:28.206
- No, I didn't.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.582
- Mnh-mnh-mnh.

12:29.624 --> 12:31.126
- [John Doe] I didn't.
I'm a replacement.

12:31.167 --> 12:34.045
You can check
my milkman placard?

12:34.087 --> 12:38.925
- This is my friend,
dendrocnide moriodes.

12:38.967 --> 12:41.219
His nickname is
Mr. Gympie-Gympie.

12:41.261 --> 12:45.807
The nettle so nice
they named him twice.

12:45.849 --> 12:47.976
He's not so nice
when you touch him, though.

12:48.018 --> 12:50.895
I've heard it's like
licking a live wire,

12:50.937 --> 12:56.109
or taking an acid shower,
or going into cardiac arrest.

12:56.151 --> 13:00.363
I wonder what it'll
feel like for you.

13:02.365 --> 13:03.616
- No.

13:03.658 --> 13:07.662
[screaming]

13:07.704 --> 13:10.707
- All I hear
is buzzing,

13:10.749 --> 13:14.794
but you aren't
a helpful little bee, are you?

13:14.836 --> 13:18.340
You're a locust,
a holy man,

13:18.381 --> 13:24.971
reveling and eating
and killing and fucking.

13:25.013 --> 13:30.143
Thankfully, I am a firm believer
in the power of recycling.

13:33.897 --> 13:36.524
- Granny, she's sick.

13:36.566 --> 13:37.692
- Okay.

13:37.734 --> 13:38.943
- No, no, no, no, no.
It's true.

13:38.985 --> 13:40.862
The medicine is for her.
You don't believe me,

13:40.904 --> 13:43.365
you can look in my pocket,
right there.

13:43.406 --> 13:44.324
[grunting]
- What are you--

13:44.366 --> 13:45.492
[sighs]

13:58.505 --> 14:00.215
Open.

14:00.256 --> 14:01.800
Chew.

14:01.841 --> 14:04.052
Okay, good.

14:04.094 --> 14:05.845
Sorry I thought
you were holy men.

14:05.887 --> 14:07.681
They're on pilgrimage,
and they're everywhere.

14:07.722 --> 14:09.099
I wouldn't.

14:09.140 --> 14:11.893
Mr. conium maculatum here
would love a chance

14:11.935 --> 14:14.020
to knock you
on your tushy.

14:14.062 --> 14:16.398
- Man,
fuck this place.

14:16.439 --> 14:21.236
- So, here is the medicine
granny requested but...

14:21.277 --> 14:24.197
[sighs]

14:24.239 --> 14:26.741
Are you sure
she wanted this?

14:26.783 --> 14:29.035
It has no
medicinal purpose.

14:29.077 --> 14:30.829
- Well, it's on the list,

14:30.870 --> 14:33.081
so maybe granny
just likes flowers.

14:33.123 --> 14:35.166
[giggles]

14:35.208 --> 14:37.502
- I never gave these
to her.

14:40.255 --> 14:43.008
Here you go.

14:43.049 --> 14:44.467
- Is it true
somebody threw you

14:44.509 --> 14:45.552
out of a moving truck?

14:48.388 --> 14:51.307
- Only because
I poisoned her first.

14:51.349 --> 14:52.475
[giggles]

14:52.517 --> 14:54.936
Watts and I have
disagreements.

14:54.978 --> 15:00.358
Plants need space
to spread their roots.

15:00.400 --> 15:01.943
[sighs]

15:01.985 --> 15:03.737
She couldn't make
room for me,

15:03.778 --> 15:07.907
so I found a place

15:07.949 --> 15:10.326
where I could have
all the space I needed,

15:10.368 --> 15:13.955
here, alone.

15:19.044 --> 15:21.171
Give my love to Granny.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.638
[bells ringing]

15:30.680 --> 15:31.973
- We can take 'em.

15:37.520 --> 15:39.356
- Nah.

15:39.397 --> 15:43.902
[engines revving]
[whooping]

15:47.697 --> 15:50.867
[bells ringing]

15:50.909 --> 15:52.202
- [Quiet]
Where are we going?

15:52.243 --> 15:54.287
- [John Doe] They've been
behind us for 50 miles,

15:54.329 --> 15:55.872
and they're only
getting closer.

15:55.914 --> 15:57.290
We gotta get off the road.

16:01.044 --> 16:03.505
[engines revving]
[whooping]

16:03.546 --> 16:04.631
