Good news!

17:14.117 --> 17:16.703
They have an absolute
classic in here!

17:24.544 --> 17:27.130
[footsteps nearing]

17:29.716 --> 17:31.384
- Is this a silent movie?

17:35.805 --> 17:38.975
- Hello, citizen.
Hop on.

17:39.017 --> 17:42.354
I'm pretty sure
I remember what happens.

17:42.395 --> 17:44.814
It doesn't look safe,
Blank Man,

17:44.856 --> 17:47.025
and why are you drooling?

17:47.067 --> 17:48.985
Well, because
you're so attractive.

17:49.027 --> 17:50.487
Hmm...

17:50.528 --> 17:54.657
I don't normally meet citizens
of the female persuasion.

17:58.078 --> 17:59.788
- [Quiet] Oh, no, my shoe!

17:59.829 --> 18:01.790
Why was I cursed
with such tiny feet?

18:01.831 --> 18:03.875
[laughing]

18:03.917 --> 18:06.544
It's your line.
- Oh, right.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.964
I have to say, I like when
you grab me like that.

18:10.006 --> 18:12.550
- How dare you
objectify me?

18:12.592 --> 18:15.470
- Oh, no, that's right.
I gotta keep it PG-13.

18:15.512 --> 18:17.806
- Yeah, you'd need a map to know
where to put it, anyway.

18:17.847 --> 18:20.975
[laughing]

18:21.017 --> 18:23.144
Do this a lot?

18:23.186 --> 18:24.562
- Only when I'm waiting
for a storm to pass

18:24.604 --> 18:26.856
or in between runs,
I'll check out a flick.

18:26.898 --> 18:29.067
I like the action ones.

18:29.109 --> 18:30.402
Feels good to
watch somebody else

18:30.443 --> 18:32.529
get shot at
for once, you know?

18:32.570 --> 18:33.863
You like the movies?

18:33.905 --> 18:35.949
- Mmm...

18:35.990 --> 18:37.450
We weren't allowed to
watch them.

18:39.869 --> 18:40.995
[chuckles]

18:41.037 --> 18:43.415
- What? Let me in
on the joke.

18:43.456 --> 18:45.667
- Okay.

18:45.709 --> 18:48.003
One time, my brother
snuck us into a theater

18:48.044 --> 18:50.005
when nobody was looking.

18:50.046 --> 18:52.298
- Rebel. How was it?

18:52.340 --> 18:53.883
- The movie?
I don't remember.

18:53.925 --> 18:56.594
It was with two cowboys
fighting a mechanical spider.

18:56.636 --> 18:58.096
- Love that.

18:58.138 --> 19:00.140
- All I remember, is how hard
my brother laughed.

19:00.181 --> 19:02.017
[laughing]

19:02.058 --> 19:03.727
He had a great laugh.

19:03.768 --> 19:05.729
It sounded like
a chainsaw.

19:05.770 --> 19:08.815
[laughing]

19:08.857 --> 19:11.609
- He sounds annoyin'.
- He was.

19:11.651 --> 19:13.403
He was so annoying.

19:15.739 --> 19:16.781
He was so annoying.

19:19.200 --> 19:21.161
It was so cold
in the theater.

19:21.202 --> 19:23.246
He let me wear his jacket.

19:23.288 --> 19:24.581
He never let me wear it.

19:26.916 --> 19:28.084
And now it's all I got.

19:32.213 --> 19:34.049
What?
- Oh, nothin'.

19:34.090 --> 19:37.385
It's just the first time we've
talked without a "motherfucker"

19:37.427 --> 19:39.387
or a "fuck you"
slipping in there.

19:39.429 --> 19:42.098
- Fuck you, motherfucker.
- That's better.

19:42.140 --> 19:44.184
[chuckles]

19:44.225 --> 19:47.145
- Who is this guy?
- Oh, this is the best part.

19:47.187 --> 19:51.107
So, do you wanna play
Michael "The Suit" Minnelli?

19:53.193 --> 19:56.446
- Ahh, look how thin
my mustache is!

19:56.488 --> 19:57.697
[laughing]

19:57.739 --> 19:58.448
- [John Doe] I'm coming to
get you, Minnelli,

19:58.490 --> 20:00.075
no matter what you say.

20:00.116 --> 20:01.826
- [Quiet]
You'll never catch me!

20:01.868 --> 20:05.121
I'm gonna sweat through
this satin set of pajamas.

20:05.163 --> 20:06.539
[laughing]

20:18.593 --> 20:31.064
**

20:31.106 --> 20:32.607
[clears throat]

20:32.649 --> 20:33.983
- Oh!

20:34.025 --> 20:36.611
Uh, hey, they have
running water,

20:36.653 --> 20:39.072
so I figured,
you know, laundry day.

20:39.114 --> 20:40.156
[chuckles]

20:44.619 --> 20:46.579
- Stop!
- What? What's wrong?

20:46.621 --> 20:48.289
- I didn't ask you
to do that.

20:48.331 --> 20:49.457
Didn't you hear what
I said last night?

20:49.499 --> 20:51.376
- Yes, you said
it was all you had,

20:51.418 --> 20:52.627
so I tried
to clean it.

20:52.669 --> 20:53.962
I was trying to do
somethin' nice.

20:54.004 --> 20:55.255
- You washed it!

20:57.507 --> 20:59.759
There's nothing left.
There's none of him left!

20:59.801 --> 21:03.972
I didn't even get to
say goodbye, but I had this.

21:04.014 --> 21:05.932
- Look,
I'm no bloodiologist,

21:05.974 --> 21:08.810
but I'm pretty sure it wasn't
just your brother's blood on it!

21:08.852 --> 21:09.853
[door slamming]

21:19.446 --> 21:20.613
- Oh, come on. You're still
not talkin' to me?

21:22.323 --> 21:26.536
- Hey, let me guess.
Amber poisoned you.

21:26.578 --> 21:28.955
What'd she use?
She use pink or purple?

21:28.997 --> 21:30.081
- The yellow.

21:30.123 --> 21:31.833
- Oh, that-that one
really sucks.

21:31.875 --> 21:33.084
- Yeah.

21:33.126 --> 21:34.753
- Thanks for
making the run.

21:34.794 --> 21:35.879
- I'm sure you're
looking forward

21:35.920 --> 21:36.963
to giving that to granny,

21:37.005 --> 21:40.091
so she can live
a long, horny life.

21:40.133 --> 21:42.093
- This won't save granny.

21:42.135 --> 21:43.553
Nothing will.

21:45.263 --> 21:49.726
This is to make granny more
comfortable as she passes on.

21:49.768 --> 21:58.568
**

21:58.610 --> 22:00.945
- Mmm.

22:00.987 --> 22:02.447
Ugh!

22:02.489 --> 22:06.368
Even with the flower in it,
it still tastes like piss.

22:06.409 --> 22:08.620
- I thought
we were helping you.

22:08.661 --> 22:11.623
- No. I got one gas pedal
in the grave.

22:11.664 --> 22:13.625
Ain't nothin'
gonna happen now.

22:13.667 --> 22:17.045
- I don't understand.
You're just gonna give up?

22:17.087 --> 22:21.049
- Kid,
you and I both know

22:21.091 --> 22:23.385
that most people
in this world,

22:23.426 --> 22:26.429
they-they don't have
the luxury of going quietly.

22:26.471 --> 22:30.058
Everybody else
goes loud--

22:30.100 --> 22:32.852
car crashes, gunfire.

22:32.894 --> 22:36.606
I heard about one
unlucky son of a bitch

22:36.648 --> 22:40.193
got swallowed up
by ants.

22:40.235 --> 22:41.486
Nah.

22:41.528 --> 22:44.698
This way, I get to go
on my own terms,

22:44.739 --> 22:47.992
and I get to do
somethin' rare.

22:48.034 --> 22:51.371
I get to say goodbye
to the people I love.

22:54.124 --> 22:57.293
Milkman,
you gave me a gift.

22:57.335 --> 23:00.380
You will be paid
in full.

23:00.422 --> 23:02.340
And as for you...

23:02.382 --> 23:05.260
[groans]

23:05.301 --> 23:06.970
I want you to have
a little somethin'.

23:08.513 --> 23:09.764
[laughing]

23:09.806 --> 23:15.020
Check out page 22,
the drive-thru.

23:15.061 --> 23:16.896
[laughing]

23:16.938 --> 23:20.316
- Jesus Christ.
- [Granny] You're welcome.

23:20.358 --> 23:22.610
Now, scram.

23:36.541 --> 23:39.919
I am the last
of the old timers.

23:39.961 --> 23:43.006
You're taking
the wheel now, Watts.

23:43.048 --> 23:46.968
So, let me give you
a nickel's worth of free advice.

23:47.010 --> 23:50.430
The only thing more-more
precious than--

23:50.472 --> 23:55.852
than gas, food,
porno, water,

23:55.894 --> 23:58.813
is time,

23:58.855 --> 24:03.360
time with the people
you care about.

24:03.401 --> 24:04.903
[crying]

24:10.283 --> 24:11.618
- Mnh-mnh.

24:14.496 --> 24:17.540
- Don't let
some dumb bullshit

24:17.582 --> 24:21.002
take that time
away from you.

24:21.044 --> 24:23.630
- Granny, you know, I--

24:23.672 --> 24:26.758
- Oh, no. No, kid.
I know. Now, go.

24:26.800 --> 24:29.177
You're gettin' saltwater
on my leather upholstery.

24:29.219 --> 24:38.395
**

24:38.436 --> 24:44.150
See ya soon, Fang.

24:44.192 --> 24:46.152
[sighs]

